<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="335" pageId="33" pageNumber="334" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[107,235,1211,1235]" box="[107,235,1211,1235]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[107,235,1211,1235]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[106,1096,1249,1363]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Small species, body length 4.8-6.0 mm. Coloration: body blackish-brown to black; elytra with moderately large reddish-yellow spot of subtriangular shape near posterior margin; middle and hind legs yellowish-brown, profemora dark-brown, protibiae and -tarsi brown; antennae reddishbrown, antennomere I infuscate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[106,1097,1379,1557]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
Head approximately 1.05 times as long as wide, widest across eyes; behind eyes convexly tapering posteriad in dorsal view, posterior angles practically obsolete (
<figureCitation box="[751,840,1410,1434]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Fig. 118</figureCitation>
); punctation very coarse and of variable density, moderately sparse to dense; interstices without microsculpture; eyes large and bulging, 0.7-0.8 times the length of postocular region from posterior margin of eyes to neck in dorsal view. Antenna moderately slender, approximately 
<quantity box="[737,819,1502,1526]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
long; antennomere X approximately 1.5 times as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[106,1096,1571,1656]" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">
Pronotum slender, approximately 1.35 times as long as broad and 0.90-0.95 times as broad as head (
<figureCitation box="[169,259,1601,1626]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="334">Fig. 118</figureCitation>
); punctation as coarse as that of head and moderately sparse; impunctate midline of variable width; interstices without microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" startId="34.[192,229,757,779]" targetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" targetPageId="34">
<paragraph blockId="34.[192,1174,757,832]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,321,757,779]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 118-123:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Assing, 2010" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2010" box="[329,569,757,778]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipeniculatum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[329,569,757,778]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Lobrathium bipeniculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[576,628,757,778]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: forebody (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[737,770,758,774]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">118</emphasis>
); male tergite VIII (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[963,996,758,775]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">119</emphasis>
); male sternite VII (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,234,787,803]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">120</emphasis>
); male sternite VIII (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[433,465,787,802]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">121</emphasis>
); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,925,787,804]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">122-123</emphasis>
). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="34.[190,1179,861,916]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
Elytra long, approximately 1.05 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[811,901,861,885]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 118</figureCitation>
); submarginal line present; punctation coarse, dense, well-defined, and arranged in more or less irregular series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,1179,930,1046]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Abdomen slightly narrower than elytra; anterior impressions of tergites I-IV with dense and coarse punctation, punctation of remainder of tergal surfaces moderately fine and moderately dense; interstices with or without shallow microsculpture, glossy; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,1180,1060,1299]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<specimenCount box="[193,206,1063,1079]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of tergite VIII indistinctly angled in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[944,1033,1060,1084]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 121</figureCitation>
); sternite VII with shallow and small median impression without pubescence, posterior margin rather strongly concave, in the middle with small convex projection (
<figureCitation box="[749,838,1121,1146]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 120</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII highly distinctive, with large, oblong median impression, this impression without pubescence (except posterior portion) or peg-setae, on either side with extensive and conspicuous cluster of long black setae, posterior excision large, deep, and broadly V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[738,827,1213,1238]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Fig. 121</figureCitation>
); aedeagus approximately 
<quantity box="[1097,1179,1214,1238]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
long, ventral process of very distinctive morphology, slender and furcate apically (lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[198,336,1275,1299]" captionStart="Figs 118-123" captionStartId="34.[192,229,757,779]" captionTargetBox="[191,1168,174,739]" captionTargetId="figure-325@34.[191,1173,174,754]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 118-123: Lobrathium bipeniculatum sp. n.: forebody (118); male tergite VIII (119); male sternite VII (120); male sternite VIII (121); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (122-123). Scale bars: 118: 1.0 mm; 119-123: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5365419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5365419/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Figs 122-123</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[190,1179,1313,1429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<specimenCount box="[195,205,1314,1332]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of tergite VIII convexly produced in the middle; sternite VIII somewhat longer than tergite VIII, posterior margin broadly and weakly convex; segments IX-X not particularly slender; tergite IX undivided anteriorly, anterior margin emarginate in the middle; tergite X of subovoid shape, not particularly slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[190,395,1458,1482]" box="[190,395,1458,1482]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[190,395,1458,1482]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Comparative notes:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[189,1180,1497,1643]" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">
This species is distinguished from all its congeners particularly by the morphology of the ventral process of the aedeagus, as well as by the shape and chaetotaxy of the male sternites VII-VIII. From other Taiwanese 
<taxonomicName box="[425,619,1558,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[425,542,1558,1576]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="335">Lobrathium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with a reddish elytral spot, it is additionally separated by the glossy abdomen and the combination of small size, coarse punctation of the head and pronotum, and long elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="336" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[106,227,175,199]" box="[106,227,175,199]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,227,175,199]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Etymology:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[106,1096,213,268]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">The specific epithet is an adjective derived from the Latin noun peniculus (brush) and refers to the conspicuous chaetotaxy of the male sternite VIII.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
